SIMPLE: expense
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expense
<hw>Ex*pense"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>expensa</ets> (sc. <ets>pecunia</ets>), or <ets>expensum</ets>, fr.
<ets>expensus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>expendere</ets>. See
<er>Expend</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A spending or consuming;
disbursement; expenditure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Husband nature's riches from <qex>expense</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is expended, laid out, or consumed; cost;
outlay; charge; -- sometimes with the notion of <xex>loss</xex> or
<xex>damage</xex> to those on whom the expense falls; <as>as, the
<ex>expenses</ex> of war; an <ex>expense</ex> of time</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Courting popularity at his party's <qex>expense</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Brougham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Loss.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And moan the <qex>expense</qex> of many a vanished sight.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Expense magazine</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a small
magazine containing ammunition for immediate use.</cd> <rj><au>H. L.
Scott.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expensefull</ent>⟦br⟧
